\pard\b 5.4 Concurrency Control\b0\par
\pard\li360\b 5.4.1 Concurrency Control Algorithms Used / Discussed\b0\par
\pard\li720\fi-360 \bullet\tab Lock-based protocol: records are locked before update so that conflicting operations cannot happen at the same time.\par
\pard\li720\fi-360 \bullet\tab Two-phase locking (2PL): a transaction first acquires all required locks and then releases them after finishing the update phase.\par
\pard\li720\fi-360 \bullet\tab Row-level locking: only the selected rows are locked, which improves concurrency.\par
\pard\li720\fi-360 \bullet\tab Table-level locking: the whole table is locked when broader protection is needed for administrative operations.\par
