\pard\b 5.5 Recovery Mechanisms\b0\par
\pard\li360\b 5.5.1 Recovery Techniques Relevant to the Project\b0\par
\pard\li720\fi-360 \bullet\tab Write-ahead logging (WAL): changes are written to the log before they are written permanently to the database.\par
\pard\li720\fi-360 \bullet\tab Undo operation: uncommitted changes are reversed after failure.\par
\pard\li720\fi-360 \bullet\tab Redo operation: committed changes are restored during recovery if needed.\par
\pard\li720\fi-360 \bullet\tab Checkpointing: periodic checkpoints reduce recovery time by limiting how far the log must be scanned.\par
\pard\li720\fi-360 \bullet\tab Backup and restore: logical or physical backups can restore the database in severe failure situations.\par
\pard\li360\b 5.5.2 Recovery Example for SecureMeal\b0\par
