\pard\b 5.6 Conclusion of Chapter 5\b0\par
\pard The SecureMeal project demonstrates how transactions, TCL commands, locking, and recovery mechanisms maintain correctness in a multi-user DBMS environment. Atomic operations such as student registration, menu updates, attendance marking, and feedback submission can be controlled safely using COMMIT, ROLLBACK, SAVEPOINT, and locks. Recovery mechanisms ensure that accidental failures do not leave the database in an inconsistent state.\par
